The paper discusses a structured and comprehensive approach to assess the "goodness" of agile methods, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the Objectives, Principles and Practices (OPP) Framework, which is related to software development (cs.SD) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the capability of the organization to support the adopted principles and practices, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
